h now starts from <code>norm2</code> cross-attention and then runs <code>norm3</code> FFN, without executing self-attention. The self-attention module and <code>norm1</code> parameters remain present so checkpoint keys and shapes are preserved.</p>\n    <p>Changed Body-Tell model construction to use <code>activation=\"relu\"</code> for the transformer decoder layer, matching VoxTell's default decoder activation.</p>\n  </section>\n\n  <section>\n    <h2>Files Changed</h2>\n    <ul>\n      <li><code>Body-Tell/body_tell/models/transformer.py</code> - removed self-attention execution from <code>TransformerDecoderLayer.forward_pre</code>.</li>\n      <li><code>Body-Tell/body_tell/models/voxtell_body_model.py</code> - switched transformer decoder layer activation from GELU to ReLU.</li>\n      <li><code>Body-Tell/tests/test_voxtell_transformer_compat.py</code> - converted the SP-A.P0 golden parity test from expected-fail to active pass/fail validation.</li>\n      <li><code>Body-Tell/reports/26-05-24/runs/SP-A.P1/RESULT.html</code> - this result report.</li>\n    </ul>\n    <p class=\"meta\">Protected files <code>lead.html</code> and <code>workflow_manifest.yaml</code> were not edited for this task.</p>\n  </section>\n\n  <section>\n    <h2>Verification</h2>\n    <p>Command run:</p>\n    <pre><code>conda run -n voxtell python -m pytest Body-Tell/tests/test_voxtell_transformer_compat.py</code></pre>\n    <p>Important output:</p>\n    <pre><code>platform linux -- Python 3.12.13, pytest-9.0.3, pluggy-1.6.0\nrootdir: /home/comp/csrkzhu/code/Hyper-Tell\ncollected 1 item\n\nBody-Tell/tests/test_voxtell_transformer_compat.py .                     [100%]\n\n============================== 1 passed in 13.90s ==============================</code></pre>\n    <p>The golden test constructs both decoders with <code>dropout=0.0</code>, loads the VoxTell reference state dict into the Body-Tell decoder, and asserts output parity at <code>atol=1e-6</code>, <code>rtol=0.0</code>.</p>\n  </section>\n\n  <section>\n    <h2>Acceptance Criteria</h2>\n    <ul>\n      <li><span class=\"ok\">Pass</span> - Transformer compatibility tests pass with dropout disabled.</li>\n      <li><span class=\"ok\">Pass</span> - No unrelated model refactor introduced; changes are limited to transformer decoder semantics and the decoder activation setting required by P1.</li>\n      <li><span class=\"ok\">Pass</span> - <code>self_attn</code>, <code>norm1</code>, and their parameter names/shapes remain in the decoder layer for checkpoint compatibility.</li>\n    </ul>\n  </section>\n\n  <section>\n    <h2>Blockers And Risks</h2>\n    <p>No blockers.</p>\n    <p class=\"warn\">Residual risk:</p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>The verification covers the transformer parity surface only. Encoder, decoder, projection, position encoding, and full VoxTell checkpoint loading remain assigned to later SP-A tasks.</li>\n      <li>The worktree already contained pre-existing changes in <code>lead.html</code>, <code>workflow_manifest.yaml</code>, and SP-A.P0 artifacts. They were left untouched.</li>\n    </ul>\n  </section>\n\n  <section>\n    <h2>Recommendation</h2>\n    <p><strong>ready_for_review</strong></p>\n  </section>\n</main>\n</body>\n</html>\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
